ment membrane disease (5% of cases)\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following conditions is most commonly associated with pauci-immune glomerulonephritis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Lupus nephritis","Eosinophilic granulomatosis with polyangiitis","Goodpasture disease","Post-streptococcal glomerulonephritis","Membranous nephropathy"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003EEosinophilic granulomatosis with polyangiitis\u003C/strong\u003E, which is a pauci-immune glomerulonephritis associated with anti-neutrophil cytoplasmic antibodies (ANCA). It is characterised by asthma, eosinophilia, and small vessel vasculitis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other conditions represent different types of glomerulonephritis:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELupus nephritis\u003C/strong\u003E is an immune complex-mediated glomerulonephritis associated with systemic lupus erythematosus\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGoodpasture disease\u003C/strong\u003E is an anti-glomerular basement membrane disease with both pulmonary and renal involvement\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPost-streptococcal glomerulonephritis\u003C/strong\u003E is an immune complex-mediated disease that occurs following infection with \u003Cem\u003EStreptococcus\u003C/em\u003E species\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMembranous nephropathy\u003C/strong\u003E is an immune complex-mediated disease often associated with phospholipase A2 receptor antibodies\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPauci-immune glomerulonephritis shows little or no immune deposits on immunofluorescence microscopy, distinguishing it from immune complex-mediated and anti-glomerular basement membrane disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Rapidly progressive glomerulonephritis can be classified into three types: pauci-immune, immune complex-mediated, and anti-glomerular basement membrane disease","Pauci-immune glomerulonephritis is most commonly associated with anti-neutrophil cytoplasmic antibody (ANCA) vasculitis syndromes","Eosinophilic granulomatosis with polyangiitis is characterised by asthma, eosinophilia, and small vessel vasculitis"],"references":["Xu PC, Chen T, Gao S, Hu SY, Wei L, Yan TK. Clinical and pathologic characteristics of pauci-immune anti-myeloperoxidase antibody associated glomerulonephritis with nephrotic range proteinuria. Ren Fail. 2018 Nov;40(1):554-560. doi: 10.1080/0886022X.2018.1487865. PMID: 30278797; PMCID: PMC6171425.","Rutgers A, Sanders JS, Stegeman CA, Kallenberg CG. Pauci-immune necrotizing glomerulonephritis. Rheum Dis Clin North Am. 2010 Aug;36(3):559-72. doi: 10.1016/j.rdc.2010.05.002. PMID: 20688250.","Juanet C, Hassi I, Koirala A. ANCA-Negative Pauci-Immune Glomerulonephritis: A Review. Glomerular Dis. 2024 Oct 11;4(1):189\u201399. doi: 10.1159/000541792. PMCID: PMC11540412.","Jennette, J. C., \u0026 D\u0027Agati, V. D. (2023). Heptinstall\u0027s Pathology of the Kidney. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53241"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15068"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53241","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53241"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-06T22:31:02+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-06T22:33:35+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7756"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67776"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":n